---
description: Use TSS for compact terminal output when exact raw output is not required.
alwaysApply: true
---

Prefer `tss run -- <command>` for terminal commands that produce large human-readable output. Do not use TSS for structured output, patches, redirected or piped commands, or any command where exact stdout/stderr is required. If TSS reports omitted output, inspect it with `tss raw <id>`.

This rule is instruction-only. Cursor terminal commands are not automatically rewritten by TSS.
